        #<#MakeVendorsGreatAgain2017>

            #<Description+Features>

                ###############################################################################################

                # By Jim Raven                                                                                #

                # Makes all vendors Great By changing whites to blues and greens to purples                   #

                # Features                                                                                    #

                # Weapon vendors Now have a 10% chance at legendary IOTD Else Purple                          #

                # Health vendors Now have a 10% chance at legendary IOTD Else Purple                          #

                # Grenade vendors Now have a 10% chance at legendary IOTD Else Purple                         #

                # Adds Relics To Grenade vendors similar to how TPS has oz kits in grenade vendors            #

                # Relics have a lower spawn chance than nades in vendors                                      #

                # Ups The quantity of grenade vendors from 3-6 to 7-8                                         #

                # Added option to not have relics in grenade vendors                                          #

                # Install using LightChaosMan's Filter tool! Unless you know how to merge Hotfixes yourself   #

                # This mod was made from scratch to finish with Light's Tool so a huge thanks to you good sir.#

                ###############################################################################################

            #</Description+Features>

        #<BL2 No Wasted COMs>

            # BL2 No Wasted COMs v1.0.0

            # Licensed under Public Domain / CC0 1.0 Universal

            #

            # Sets the game to only drop COMs for the player classes who are actually

            # in the game at the time.  Once a player class has joined the game, the

            # only way to remove that character's COMs from the drop pools is to exit

            # to the main menu and re-execute the patch.

            #<Initial Clear>

                # Do an initial set to clear out the COM item pools.  This is actually

                # only required if you're looking to "clear out" a pool after a character's

                # left the game, and must be done by exiting out to the main menu and re-

                # executing the mod/patch.

        #<NoMuzzleflashes>

            - Removes muzzleflashes from the game, because I like seeing stuff

            - Looks a bit weird, but you'll get used to it.

            #<Guns>

                #<Assault Rifles>

                    #<Default>

                        set GD_Weap_AssaultRifle.Effects.AR_Default_MuzzleFlashes ParticleEffects ()

                    #</Default>

                    #<E-Tech>

                    #</E-Tech>

                #</Assault Rifles>

        #<Rarity Color Fix>

            #NoMoreJebaited

            By Koby

            Image Album: https://imgur.com/a/AEZNy

            Changes the rarity color of unique aftermarket items to a dark teal to be more distinguishable from other items.

            Changes the color of Moxxi weapons to a blood red.

            Supports Gemstone weapons from the Unofficial Community Patch.

            Changes the order of items in the inventory: Pearl -> Seraph -> (Unique Uniques if enabled) -> Legendary -> Moxxi -> Unique -> Gemstone -> E-Tech -> Very Rare...

            Has an optional module to turn all Heads and Skins to a grey-ish color.

            Has an optional module to turn all Legendary items which don't world drop into Dark Orange items (Unique Uniques).

            Also changes the color of Moxxi weapons to a blood red.

            Has 2 money color options: Mint green money (default) and normal yellow.

            Full Filter Tool support!

            Thanks to Dave for providing the Rarity Colors resource.

            Also thanks to FromDarkHell for writing me a script for the Heads and Skins.

            INCOMPATIBILITY NOTE:

            This mod will most likely conflict with any mod which changes rarity colors and rarities of items.

            If you have basic modding and reading knowledge, you can fix the rarity in the weapon/item mod yourself.

            #<Rarity Color Change (Pick your Money Color here)><MUT>

                #<Rarity Color Change (Yellow Money)>
